				\begin{document}$$\sigma_{\text{GE}}^{2}$$\end{document} is the genotype × environment interaction, σ2 is the error variance, (l) is the number of environments and (r) is the number of replications in each trials. The genetic correlations among traits corresponded to the ratio between the genotypic covariance for each pair of traits and the product of the respective genotypic standard deviation. The phenotypic correlations among traits were calculated as simple Pearson’s correlation coefficients based on adjusted and standardised phenotypic data.

